Canadian government has expressed concern over the excessive use of force on End SARS protesters. The government said this while condemning the shooting of protesters at Lekki tollgate and others during the protest across the country. Canada further called on the Buhari-led administration to bring to book those responsible for the human right violations and abuse in Nigeria. A tweet by Canada’s Foreign Policy reads, “Canada is deeply concerned about the excessive use of force during the ongoing protests in #Nigeria. “Those responsible for #HumanRights violations and abuse must be held accountable.” <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-850852" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/IMG_8308.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="1334" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/IMG_8308.jpg 750w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/IMG_8308-169x300.jpg 169w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/IMG_8308-576x1024.jpg 576w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px">